<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0898 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book provides an overview of computational methods as well as astheir application to problems of molecular biophysics. Seven chaptersdeal with the methodology, enzymes and other proteins, nucleic acids,carbohydrates, hydration and hydrophobic effects concerning biomolecularsystems. Several comparisons of theoretical and experimental resultsallow the reader to judge the reliability of various computational methodsand molecular models.</TEXT></DOC>